title: I can't update, although I can still log in and play on 6.16.
body: I open lol client. It says "Unespecified error occured. Please check the logs for more information." then I click retry and it gives me the same mesage. If i close the message, I can just log in like normal and play on 6.16. I can even q for matches. I went into a custom however, to check if I was on 6.17 or not, so i played vayne, hit lvl 3 and put 2 points in q and sitll had a 35% ad scaling instead of the new 40%.

replies.body: This is a peculiar issue, because 6.17 isn't out yet!  If you are still having this issue,  provide screenshots and any additional information if possible.  Let me know!

ya it just tells me the update failed and it scans for files. I have to close and open the lol client several times and see if i get lucky for the client to say launch and not update failed. It also says in the bottom right corner of the unlaunched client patch 6.17.
The bottom right just posts a link to the patch notes, which is something we usually put out before the patch rolls out.  At what percent of the patcher are you receiving an error; 0?

it doesnt even start loading. the client instantly pops up and says update failed and the scanning files is stuck at 1 percent. Fortunately i was able to get around it by opening the client several times until the launch button appeared.

for me at 0%.
it says 1 file scanned whenever i cancel the error message and it does not scan anything more or update. do you have any suggestions?
in about how much time will the server start updating?
